An '''iron founder''' (also '''iron-founder''' or '''ironfounder''') is a worker in molten [[ferrous]] metal, generally working within an [[iron foundry]].<ref>[https://archive.org/details/theironfoundersu00boll "The iron founder" supplement. A complete illustrated exposition of the art of casting in iron. Also, the founding of statues; the art of taking casts, pattern modelling; useful formulas and tables (1893)]</ref> 

Historically the appellation "founder" was given to the supervisor of a [[blast furnace]], and persons who made castings in iron or other heavy metal.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=bq5XAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false Edward Hazen, Reuben S. Gilbert, Abraham John Mason, John Ludlow Morton, Stephen H. Gimber, Raphael Hoyle, Charles Burton Uriah Hunt, 1837]</ref> The term is also often applied to the company or works in which an iron foundry operates.

